AOT IN FAVORS OF SIR ROBERT MURRAY OF ABERGAIRNIE AND OTHER HERITORS UPON THE POW OF INCHAFFRAY. OCTOBER 9, 1690.

AT EDINBURGH the ninth day of October one thousand six hundred and ninety six years Anent the Petition given in and presented to His Majesties High Commis- sioner and the Honourable Estates of Parliament by Sir Robert Mur-ray of Aber- eairnie Sir Patrick Murray of Auchtertyre Mungo Graham of Gorthie and J ames Oliphant of Williamstoun Heritors upon the Pow of Inchaffray, Humbly Shewing that the said Pow of Inehaffray being a long tract of levell ground subject to unseaf- sonable inundations and overflowings of the water wherby the adjacent ground and meadows become marish and the grass and coms of severall Heritors of the saids Lands are frequently lost and rendered useless The draining and ditehing wherof in a convenient and effectuall manner might not only prevent the saids Losses and damnages sustained by the Heritors but likewayes be a mean of considerable improvement of so large a tract of ground to the great advantage and utility of all concerned And the Petitioners Predecessors with other Heritors upon the said Pow haveing endeavoured by Submissions Decreits arbitrall and otherwayes to adjust the differences that might arise in carrieing on and consumating so good a work their designes therin have been hitherto frustrat partly by minority of some of the Heri— tors eoncerned and partly by the dissenting of others that conceived they might have
